[h1] Headings

[p] Three heading levels, each with a distinct style:

[code-]
[h1] Page Title    <- custom wide font, white, underlined
[h2] Section       <- default font, blue, underlined
[h3] Sub-section   <- default font, blue
[-code]

[h2] align

[p] All headings support align= with values left (default), center, or right:

[code-]
[h1 align=center] Centered page title
[h2 align=right]  Right-aligned section
[h3 align=left]   Left-aligned (default)
[-code]

[h2] font

[p] Override the font on any heading using font=id:

[code-]
[h1 font=fancy]              Title in a custom font
[h2 font=fancy align=center] Custom font and centered
[-code]

[p] See [link- file=how-to/font.podweb]the font page[-link] for how to declare custom fonts.

